[0.016, "o", "\u001b[3J\u001b[H\u001b[2J"]
[0.000, "o", "\r\n"]
[0.000, "o", "  DedrooM Self-Healing Demo\r\n  =========================\r\n\r\n"]
[1.008, "o", "  This demo shows what happens when an AI agent\r\n  keeps making the same failing tool call.\r\n\r\n  The agent calls write_file() with the same args\r\n"]
[0.000, "o", "  and gets 'permission denied' each time.\r\n\r\n"]
[4.071, "o", "\r\n  ╔═══════════════════════════════════════════════════╗\r\n  ║         DedrooM Self-Healing Demo                ║\r\n  ╚═══════════════════════════════════════════════════╝\r\n\r\n"]
[0.013, "o", "  Tool:     write_file({\"path\":\"/tmp/deploy.yaml\"})\r\n  Scenario: Agent keeps failing with the same call\r\n\r\n  --- Call 1: First attempt -------------------------\r\n"]
[0.001, "o", "  Call #1: verdict=0 (ALLOW)\r\n  --- Call 2: Same call, still failing --------------\r\n"]
[0.000, "o", "  Call #2: verdict=0 (ALLOW)\r\n  --- Call 3: Still looping --------------------------\r\n"]
[0.000, "o", "  Call #3: verdict=2 (BLOCK_RETRY) [BLOCKED]\r\n  --- Call 4: Blocked with healing hint --------------\r\n"]
[0.000, "o", "  Call #4: verdict=2 (BLOCK_RETRY) [BLOCKED]\r\n  >> Healing hint injected:\r\n  >>   Adapting strategy — Use `edit_file` to make targeted edits instead of overwriting the entire file. This may break the loop pattern.\r\n\r\n  --- Call 5: Agent adapts (different path) ----------\r\n"]
[0.000, "o", "  Call #5: verdict=0 (ALLOW)\r\n\r\n  --- Self-Healing Stats -----------------------------\r\n  Mutation attempts:  0\r\n  Success rate:       0%\r\n\r\n  --- Compression Demo -------------------------------\r\n"]
[0.001, "o", "  SmartCrusher (JSON, 10 rows):\r\n    186 -> 48 tokens  (26% of original, 3 rows kept)\r\n"]
[0.001, "o", "  CodeCompressor (Rust, 2 functions):\r\n    106 -> 32 tokens  (30% of original)\r\n"]
[0.000, "o", "  LogCompressor (20 lines, repetitive):\r\n    233 -> 233 tokens  (100% of original)\r\n\r\n  --- Summary ----------------------------------------\r\n  Self-healing detects repeated failing calls,\r\n  blocks them before they waste tokens, and injects\r\n  context-aware hints to help the agent adapt.\r\n\r\n  Compression reduces redundant tool output by\r\n  60-95% before it reaches the LLM, saving tokens\r\n  on every call.\r\n\r\n"]
[0.000, "o", "  ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════\r\n"]
[0.002, "o", "\r\n\r\n"]
[1.006, "o", "  Key takeaways:\r\n  - Call #3 was BLOCKED (wasted tokens avoided)\r\n"]
[0.000, "o", "  - Call #4 got a healing hint injected into context\r\n"]
[0.000, "o", "  - Call #5 with different args was ALLOWED (no false positive)\r\n"]
[0.000, "o", "  - Compression saved 70-74% on tool output\r\n"]
[0.000, "o", "\r\n"]
[2.008, "o", "  Demo complete.\r\n"]
[0.000, "x", "0"]
